  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth 1.7.3`\r\nOS & Version: OSX High Sierra\r\nCommit hash : not yet\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\non the geth console,\r\n\r\n1. miner.start() without unlock\r\n2. mining not start with warning\r\n- `WARN [01-17|21:53:20] Block sealing failed err=\"authentication needed: password or unlock\"`\r\n3. personal.unlockAccount(eth.coinbase) and input Passphrase\r\n4. mining.start() again\r\n5. mining start successfully\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n1. miner.start() without unlock\r\n2. mining not start with warning\r\n- `WARN [01-17|21:53:20] Block sealing failed err=\"authentication needed: password or unlock\"`\r\n3. personal.unlockAccount(eth.coinbase) and input Passphrase\r\n4. mining.start() again\r\n5. nothing changed, still not start mining \r\n6. for the start mining, mining.stop() and mining.start() \r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nI think if change code of `Start` and `Stop` of `miner/miner.go` about atomic section, It can solve this problem and we can start without stop, and restart\r\n\r\ncould I fix this?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
